FIGURE 3 <::An image showing a metallic orthopedic implant component, possibly an acetabular cup, with a rod-like element inserted into it. Two black arrows indicate specific points: one points to the insertion point of the rod into the cup, and the other points to an internal feature within the cup.::> ## STEP 4 To remove the Ultamet insert from the shell, impact the extraction handle lightly one to two times. The resulting vibration will release the taper lock between the Ultamet insert and the Pinnacle shell. The insert will be lifted out of the shell by the suction cup mechanism (FIGURE 4). <::An image showing a spoon and a fork. The fork is positioned with its tines inside the bowl of the spoon. Two black arrows point to the inner edges of the spoon's bowl.::> FIGURE 2 STEP 3 Push down the attached lever with thumb pressure to engage the suction cup to the inner diameter of the Ultamet insert (FIGURE 3). <::A close-up view of a medical instrument, possibly an orthopedic reamer or inserter, engaging with a component of a hip implant, likely an acetabular cup. The instrument has a handle-like top and a spherical end that fits into the cup. A black arrow indicates a rotational or insertion direction on the instrument. The implant component is seated within a bone structure, possibly a pelvis. FIGURE 4::> PROTECTED DOCUMENT. DOCUMENT SUBJECT TO PROTECTIVE ORDER.
